[[File:Barbara04BW.jpg|thumb|Barbara Vanderlinden]] '''Barbara Vanderlinden''' is an art critic, editor and curator.
More recently, she has served as Professor of Exhibition Studies and Director of the Exhibition Laboratory at the [[University of the Arts Helsinki]] (Taideyliopisto) in Finland where she organized ''Laboratory of Hearing''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Laboratory of Hearing |work=Art & Education |year=2015 |url=http://www.artandeducation.net/announcement/laboratory-of-hearing-launches-exhibition-laboratory/ |accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref> Previously, she was Visiting Professor and initiator of the International Curatorial Programme (2001)<ref>{{cite web |title=Gwangju Biennale International Curator Course |work=Art & Education |url=http://www.artandeducation.net/announcement/gwangju-biennale-international-curator-course/ |accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref> at the [[Gwangju Biennale]] Foundation, Gwangju, South Korea, and Associate Professor of curatorial studies for the [[Center for Curatorial Studies and Art in Contemporary Culture|CCS]] Bard Master of Arts Program in Curatorial Studies in Annandale-on-Hudson, New York, Professor of Exhibition and Museum Studies (2005-2007) at the [[San Francisco Art Institute]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.artandeducation.net/announcement/sfai-an-interdisciplinary-and-transnational-approach-to-education-in-art-and-culture/|title=SFAI: An interdisciplinary and transnational approach to education in art and culture {{!}} Art & Education|website=Art & Education|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref>
In 1999, she co-curated the [[Laboratorium (art exhibition)|Laboratorium]] exhibition (with [[Hans-Ulrich Obrist|Hans Ulrich Obrist]]).<ref>{{cite journal|last=Bishop|first=Claire|year=2004|title=Antagonism and Relational Aesthetics|url=http://www.mitpressjournals.org/doi/abs/10.1162/0162287042379810#.VqJzvm70-B4|volume=Fall 2004|issue=110|pages=51–79|via=|work=[[October (journal)|October]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Holmes|first1=Brian|title=The Artistic Device, Or the Articulation of Collective Speech|url=http://www.16beavergroup.org/drift/readings/bh_artistic_device.pdf|accessdate=19 November 2016}}</ref> She served as director of the 2008 [[Brussels]] [[Biennale|Biennial]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Première Biennale de Bruxelles |language=French |work=[[La Libre Belgique]] |date=11 September 2008 |url=http://www.lalibre.be/regions/bruxelles/premiere-biennale-de-bruxelles-51b89f16e4b0de6db9b3848f |accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref> and organised multiple exhibitions as well as various international [[biennale]]s including the ''Taipei Biennial: Do You Believe in Reality?'' in 2004 at the [[Taipei Fine Arts Museum]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/10/29/style/taipeis-artistic-take-on-reality.html|title=Taipei's artistic take on reality|last=Gluck|first=Caroline|date=2004-10-29|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tfam.museum/Exhibition/Exhibition_page.aspx?id=161&ddlLang=en-us|title=TFAM {{!}} Home {{!}} Exhibitions {{!}} The 2004 Taipei Biennial ：Do You Believe in Reality?|last=group|first=臺北市10461中山北路三段181號, 181 ZhongShan North Road Section 3 Taipei 10461 Taiwan, telephone +886-2-2595-7656, info@tfam.gov.tw, TFAM media|website=www.tfam.museum|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chinapost.com.tw/news/2004/10/23/53674/Taipei-Biennial.htm|title=Taipei Biennial adds new perspectives|newspaper=www.ChinaPost.com.tw|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref> ''[[Manifesta|Manifesta 2]],'' European biennial of contemporary art (1997),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://frieze.com/article/all-together-now?language=en|title=All Together Now|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref> ''Generation Z'' at [[MoMA PS1]] in New York,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://momaps1.org/exhibitions/view/233|title=MoMA PS1: Exhibitions: Generation Z|website=momaps1.org|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zingmagazine.com/zing10/ps1/index.html|title=zingmagazine10{{!}}PS1 Contemporary Art Center{{!}}Generation Z|website=www.zingmagazine.com|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref> and ''Two Hours Wide, Two Hours Long 58/98'' at [[Cultural Centre of Belém]] in Lisbon. In 2002 she co-curated with [[Boris Groys]] ''The Art Judgement Show''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dewitteraaf.be/artikel/detail/nl/2493|title=De Witte Raaf|website=www.dewitteraaf.be|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref> and in 2000 she was co-curating with Adriano Pedrosa, Ivo Mesquita, Cuauhtemoc Medina, Louise Neri and Lilian Tone the defunct 25th [[São Paulo Art Biennial]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq26089917.htm|title=25ª Bienal de SP define seus curadores|last=|first=|date=26 August 1999|website=[[Folha de S.Paulo]]|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref>
Vanderlinden is the author of a reference book in the field of exhibitions and biennials stories in Europe called ''The Manifesta Decade: Debates on Contemporary Art Exhibitions and Biennials in Post-Wall Europe'' (MIT Press, 2005)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://frieze.com/article/manifesta-decade|title=The Manifesta Decade|website=frieze.com|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref> and co-author (with [[Francesco Bonami]] and [[Nancy Spector]]) of ''Maurizio Cattelan'' (Phaidon Press, 2003).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://de.phaidon.com/store/art/maurizio-cattelan-9780714843063/|title=Maurizio Cattelan {{!}} Art {{!}} Phaidon Store|website=Phaidon|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref>
