The '''Bell-boy Jacket''' is modeled on uniforms traditionally worn by hotel [[bell-boy]]s and [[Courier|messenger]]s, consisting of a very fitted waist-length jacket and a band collar, often double-breasted and trimmed with fancy braid or piping, and rows of close-set brass buttons. The cuffs of the jacket often have similar decoration. The style is based on 19th-century military dress uniforms and drummer boys.

