{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=September 2017}} {{Refimprove|date=May 2008}} {{infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Parti Parikatha | title_orig = | translator = | image = <!--prefer 1st edition--> | caption = | author = [[Phanishwar Nath Renu]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[India]] | language = [[Hindi language|Hindi]] | series = | genre = [[Novel]] | publisher = | release_date = 1957 | english_release_date = | media_type = | pages = | isbn = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Parti Parikatha''''' (Story of the Barren soil), is a Hindi novel written by [[Phanishwar Nath Renu]]. The story revolves around a motley group of characters in a remote village of North Eastern Bihar in the backdrop of Zamindari (landlordism) Abolition movement.
